            <p>
Foods to avoid if you are allergic to nuts<br />
                <br />
If you are allergic to nuts, you should read food labels carefully because they can often contain traces of nuts.<br />
                <br />
                </p>

<h2>Carefully check the nutritional information to avoid eating them if they include any of these ingredients or if you are going to eat any of the foods in the table below.<br />
               </h2> <br />
            <p>
- Arachis, peanuts or tree nuts<br />
                <br />
- Almonds<br />
                <br />
- Brazil nuts<br />
                <br />
- Cashew nuts<br />
                <br />
- Hazelnuts<br />
                <br />
- Sunflower seeds<br />
                <br />
- Pistachios<br />
                <br />
- Sprockets<br />
                <br />
- Chestnuts<br />
                <br />
- Nuts<br />
                <br />
- Pecan nut<br />
                <br />
- American Hard Nut<br />
                <br />
- Macadamia nut<br />
                <br />
- Nu-Nuts (peanuts that have had the taste removed and the flavour of a nut such as pecan or walnut added)<br />
                <br />
- Pastes and creams containing nuts (e.g. almond paste, Nocilla, Nutella)<br />
                <br />
- Nut butter (almond, cashew, peanut)<br />
                <br />
- Seed oil ( sunflower oil )<br />
                <br />
- Names such as "emulsified" or "satay" (peanut sauce, which could indicate that the food was thickened with peanuts)<br />
                <br />
- Foods using extracts with added artificial flavour or imitation<br />
                <br />
- Confectionery and bakery products (sponge cakes, seed breads, etc.) containing nuts.<br />
                <br />
- Ethnic foods, commercial baked goods and sweets that may be contaminated with nuts as they are frequently used in these types of foods.<br />
                <br />
- Sauces (barbecue, pesto, English, satay..), cereals, crackers, ice cream, nougat, marzipan, almond paste, chocolates<br />
                <br />
                </p>
            <h2>
Special care should be taken in Asian restaurants (peanut-based satay sauce) or buffet-style restaurants where serving spoons are put in and taken out of several trays that may contain nuts or seeds and may cause an allergic reaction by cross-contamination between foods.<br />
                <br />
            </h2>
